And listen to me: if

from this moment on you say even one word, if you speak to anyone at all,

beware of me!

The man over the orchestra turned

from it and bowed deeply, spreading his arms wide, and Margarita, smiling,

waved her hand to him.

The master, already drunk with the impending ride, flung some book

from the shelf on to the table, ruffled its pages in the flame of the tablecloth,

and the book blazed up merrily.

When the wind blew the cloak away

from the master’s legs, Margarita saw the stars of spurs on his jackboots,

now going out, now lighting up.
